Trinobantes, {een} This from the mention of the Colonia (Camulo- dunum) must refer to the revolt of the Iceni under Boudicca in Nero's reign. If so, the Trinobantes, not the Brigantes, were associated in the outbreak with the Iceni. I have therefore followed Ritter and others in adopting Trinobantes instead of Brigantes, the reading of the MSS.; for although these last are said (A. xii. 32) to have risen, they could. hardly have taken any pait in this revolt under Boudicca, or be in- cluded in the ‘qui alii nondum ser- vitio facti' of A. xiV. 31.
